v|publisher=Hum Tv|website=YouTube|date=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 16\n |Title           = Bin Roye Episode 16\n |DirectedBy      = [[Haissam Hussain]]<br/>[[Shahzad Kashmiri]]<br/>[[Momina Duraid]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Shiraz Uppal]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|1|15}}\n |ShortSummary     = \n----\n''Episodic reference'':<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9h9s0_N8t7k|title=Bin Roye Episode 16 - 15th January 2017 - Hum Tv|publisher=Hum Tv|website=YouTube|date=15 January 2017}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 17\n |Title           = Bin Roye Episode 17\n |DirectedBy      = [[Haissam Hussain]]<br/>[[Shahzad Kashmiri]]<br/>[[Momina Duraid]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Shiraz Uppal]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|1|22}}\n |ShortSummary     = \n----\n''Episodic reference'':<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PaT6r7oPBbA|title=Bin Roye Episode 17 - 22nd January 2017 - Hum Tv|publisher=Hum Tv|website=YouTube|date=22 January 2017}}</ref>\n |LineColor       = 000000\n}}\n}}\n\n==Music==\nThe soundtrack of the series is adapted from [[Bin Roye|the film]]. The original soundtrack of the series is \"Bin Roye\", that is penned by Shakeel Sohail, and composed and sung by [[Shiraz Uppal]].\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| collapsed = no\n| title2 = Bin Roye\n| extra2 = [[Shiraz Uppal]]\n| lyrics2 = Shakeel Sohail\n| length2 = 4:30\n| title3 = Ballay Ballay\n| extra3 = Shiraz Uppal, [[Harshdeep Kaur]]\n| lyrics3 = Shakeel Sohail\n| length3 = 4:08\n| title4 = Tery Bin Jeena\n| extra4 = [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]], Saleema Jawwad\n| lyrics4 = [[Sabir Zafar]]\n| length4 = 3:57\n| title5 = Chan Chariya\n| extra5 = [[Rekha Bhardwaj]]\n| lyrics5 = Sabir Zafar\n| length5 = 3:42\n| title6 = Maula Maula\n| extra6 = [[Abida Parveen]], [[Zeb Bangash]]\n| lyrics6 = Sabir Zafar\n| length6 = 4:03\n| title7 = O Yara\n| extra7 = [[Ankit Tiwari]]\n| lyrics7 = Sabir Zafar\n| length7 = 3:35\n}}\n\n==Broadcast==\n''Bin Roye'' was originally scheduled to release between April\u2013July 2016,<ref name=\"HIP2016\"/> but latter it was announced that it would be released after [[Eid-ul-Adha|2016 Eid-ul-Adha]].<ref name=BRdetails/> In August 2016, first trailer for series was released and on 20 September 2016 it was announced that series would on air its pilot episode on 2 October 2016, airing weekly episode on Sundays at 8:00&nbsp;p.m.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bin Roye teaser shows the younger side of Irtiza and Saba| url=http://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1150599/bin-royes-2nd-teaser-shows-the-younger-side-of-irtiza-and-saba|first=Hareem|last=Zafar|publisher= HIP|date=26 August 2016|accessdate=1 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception and ratings==\n''Bin Roye'' received positive reviews with most praising Humayun Saeed's performance. Writing for ''[[Dawn News]]'', Sheeba Khan wrote, \"''Bin Roye''{{'}}s TV version fills in plot holes the movie couldn't\" and expressed \"Humayun Saeed was flawless and his chemistry with Mahira Khan was very evident. He easily fit the typical Farhat Ishtiaq character: kind, really good-looking, and successful. The comfort level and the bond that needed to be shown between Saba and Irtiza was easily visualized, thanks to the directors and actors.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Bin Roye's TV version fills in plot holes the movie couldn't |url=http://images.dawn.com/news/1176358 |first=Sheeba| last=Khan|publisher=[[Dawn News]]|date=4 October 2016|accessdate =5 October 2016}}</ref> Saira Khan of ''HipInPakistan'' praised Humayun Saeed's performance, saying \"He is the undisputed king of romantic plays. No other actor can play a romantic hero as well as him\" and also praised Mahira Khan's performance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bin Roye proves why Humayun Saeed is the undisputed romantic hero|url=https://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1150933|first=Saira|last=Khan|publisher=HIP|date=19 October 2016|accessdate =19 October 2016}}</ref> Fatima Awan of ''Reviewit.pk'' wrote, \"The power-packed performances of Humayun Saeed and Mahira Khan proved how much potential this drama had if the story had more substance.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://reviewit.pk/bin-roye-episode-14-review-irtiza-in-action/|date=14 September 2019|accessdate=14 September 2019|title=Bin Roye Episode 14 Review \u2013 Irtiza In Action!|website=reviewit.pk}}</ref>\n\nThe rating of ''Bin Roye'' (blockbuster) made a huge in UK. According to ''BizAsia'', the first episode of the series was watched by 65,200 viewers at 20:00 \u2013 peaking at 94,300 viewers. The Sunday night slot on the channel is proving a success for the channel after the departure of \u2018Udaari\u2019 last week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Overnights: \u2018Bin Roye\u2019 makes splash in UK {{!}} BizAsia Media {{!}} The UK's only Asian media news site|url=http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/overnights-bin-roye-makes-splash-in-uk-on-hum-tv-2016|website=www.media247.co.uk|accessdate=9 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010044355/http://www.media247.co.uk/bizasia/overnights-bin-roye-makes-splash-in-uk-on-hum-tv-2016|archive-date=10 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> The drama gained several other high ratings both in Pakistan and U.K. throughout the 17 weeks it aired.{{fact|date=January 2020}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2016 in Pakistani television]] \n* [[List of programs broadcast by Hum TV]]\n{{Portal bar|Television}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.hum.tv/binroye/ Official Website]\n* {{facebook|binroyethedrama|''Bin Roye''}}\n\n{{Hum TV Programs|state=collapsed}}\n{{Hum Network Limited}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bin Roye}}\n[[Category:Hum TV series]]\n[[Category:2010s Pakistani television series]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Pakistani drama television series]]\n[[Category:Pakistani romantic drama television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by MD Productions]]\n[[Category:Television series based on the novels of Farhat Ishtiaq]]\n[[Category:Television series created by Momina Duraid]]\n[[Category:Pakistani telenovelas]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television dramas based on novels]]\n[[Category:Serial drama television series]]\n[[Category:2016 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Television series set in Lahore]]\n[[Category:Television series set in Punjab, Pakistan]]\n[[Category:2017 Pakistani television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the TV series based on a novel [[Bin Roye Ansoo (novel)|of similar name]]|the film adaptation|Bin Roye}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Bin Roye \n| image                    = File:Official Title Screen of Bin Roye.png\n| alt                      = Against a brownish-golden mix background, television series name in dull golden is written in Nastaliq-style font of Urdu.\n| caption                  = Title screen \n| genre                    = [[Family drama]]<br/>[[Serial drama]]<br/>[[Romantic drama]]\n| creator                  = [[Momina Duraid]] \n| writer                   = [[Farhat Ishtiaq]]\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Bin Roye Ansoo (novel)|Bin Roye Ansoo]]''|[[Farhat Ishtiaq]]}} \n| director                 = [[Haissam Hussain]]<br/>[[Shahzad Kashmiri]]<br/>Momina Duraid<!--Do not delete in end credits Momina name is there--> \n| starring                 = [[Humayun Saeed]]<br/>[[Mahira Khan]]<br/>[[Armeena Khan]] \n| theme_music_composer     = [[Shiraz Uppal]]\n| opentheme                = \"Bin Roye\" by<br/>[[Shiraz Uppal]]\n| composer                 = MAD Music \n| country                  = Pakistan\n| language                 = [[Urdu]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 17\n| list_episodes            =  \n| producer             