, Joe. 2003. ''Florida's Seminole Wars: 1817\u20131858''. Charleston, South Carolina: Arcadia Publishing. {{ISBN|0-7385-2424-7}}.\n*{{cite journal|last=Kruse|first=Paul|title=A Secret Agent in East Florida: General George Matthews and the Patriot War|journal=The Journal of Southern History|date=May 1952|volume=18|issue=2|pages=193\u2013217|jstor=2954272|doi=10.2307/2954272}} \n*Lacey, Michael O., Maj. 2002. \"Military Commissions: A Historical Survey\". ''The Army Lawyer'', March, 2002. Department of the Army Pam. 27-50-350. P. 42. at [https://web.archive.org/web/20070811065348/https://www.jagcnet.army.mil/JAGCNETINTERNET/HOMEPAGES/AC/ARMYLAWYER.NSF/c82df279f9445da185256e5b005244ee/bdfd1fe5ff1ccf5985256e5b0054d1fd/$FILE/Article%204.pdf The Judge Advocate General's Corps, U.S. Army] \u2013 URL retrieved May 9, 2008.\n*[[John K. Mahon|Mahon, John K.]] 1967. ''History of the Second Seminole War''. Gainesville, Florida: University of Florida Press.\n*Milanich, Jerald T. 1995. ''Florida Indians and the Invasion from Europe''. [[Gainesville, Florida]]: The University Press of Florida. {{ISBN|0-8130-1360-7}}.\n*Missall, John and Mary Lou Missall. 2004. ''The Seminole Wars: America's Longest Indian Conflict''. University Press of Florida. {{ISBN|0-8130-2715-2}}.\n*{{Cite journal|last=Monaco|first=Chris|date=Summer 2000|title=Fort Mitchell and the Settlement of the Alachua Country|journal=The Florida Historical Quarterly|volume=79|issue=1|pages=1\u201325|jstor=30149405}}\n*[[Office of the Chief of Military History]], United States Army. 2001. [http://www.history.army.mil/books/AMH/AMH-07.htm Chapter 7: \"The Thirty Years' Peace\"]. ''[http://www.history.army.mil/books/AMH/amh-toc.htm American Military History]''. P. 153.\n*Officers of 1-5 FA. 1999. ''1st Battalion, 5th Field Artillery Unit History''. P. 17. at <ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20070625073619/http://www.riley.army.mil/view/document.asp?ID=346-2005-03-17-34369-3#search=%22%22First%20Seminole%20War%22%20%20site%